data.title: Historical Figures Born on November 16
data.meta_description: Famous birthdays in history for the 16th of November. See which explorers, inventors and historical figures were born on November 16.
data.text:
Tiberius

Roman emperor (14 AD-37 AD), born in Rome

Leonardo Loredan, Venetian nobleman, statesman and Doge of Venice (1501-21), born in Venice (d. 1521)

Jeanne d'Albret, Queen of Navarre (1555-72), mother of French King Henry IV, born in the royal palace of Saint-Germain-en-Laye, France (d. 1572)

Joost van den Vondel, Dutch poet and dramatist (Jephtha), born in Cologne, Germany (d. 1679)

Augustyn Kordecki, Polish prior, born in Iwanowice, Kalisz, Poland (d. 1673)

Henrietta Maria, French-born daughter of Henry IV of France and Queen Consort of England (d. 1669)

Cornelis Evertsen the Youngest, Dutch admiral and buccaneer of Zeeland, born in Vlissingen, Netherlands (d. 1706)

Jean Chardin, French explorer (Middle East and India), born in Paris (d. 1713)

Joan van Hoorn, Governor-General of the Dutch East Indies (1704-09), born in Amsterdam, Dutch Republic (d. 1711)

Abraham Alewijn, Dutch poet and playwright (Puiterveense Helleveeg), born in Amsterdam (d. 1721)

Jean-Baptiste Le Rond d'Alembert

French Enlightenment philosopher and mathematician (Encyclopédie), born in Paris

Gualtherus van Doeveren, Dutch physician, and educator, born in Philippine, Zealandin Zeeuws-Vlaanderen, Netherlands (d. 1783)

Peter Andreas Heiberg, Danish author and philologist, born in Vordingborg, Denmark (d. 1841)

Petronella Moens, Frisian author and feminist, born in Kûbaard, Netherlands (d. 1843)

Étienne Pivert de Senancour, French author (Obermann), born in Paris (d. 1846)

Francis Danby, Irish painter, born in County Wexford, Ireland (d. 1861)

Charles Smith Hamilton, American Major General (Union Army), born in Westernville, New York (d. 1891)

Elliott Warren Rice, American Brevet Major General (Union Army), born in Allegheny, Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania (d. 1887)

1835 Eugenio Beltrami, Italian mathematician (non-Euclidean geometry), born in Cremona, Lombardy, Austrian Empire (d. 1900)

David Kalākaua, King of the Hawaiian Islands (1874-91), born in Honolulu, Kingdom of Hawaii (d. 1891)

Louis-Honoré Fréchette, Canadian poet, born in Lévis, Canada (d. 1908)

Jules Violle, French physicist and inventor, born in Langres, France (d. 1923)

Edmund James Flynn, Canadian politician (10th Premier of Quebec), born in Percé, Canada (d. 1927)

Jules van den Heuvel, Belgian lawyer, politician (Minister of Justice, 1899-1907), and diplomat (Ambassador to the Vatican, 1915-18), born in Ghent, Belgium (d. 1926)

Mikiel Gonzi, Roman Catholic Archbishop of Malta (1944-76), born in Vittoriosa, Birgu, Malta (d. 1984)

Philip H. Frohman, American architect (Washington National Cathedral), born in New York City (d. 1972)

Clinton Golden, American labor leader (founder of the United Steelworkers of America), born in Pottsville, Pennsylvania (d. 1961)

1888 Henri Bosco, French author and poet (Gogol), born in Avignon, France (d. 1976)

George S. Kaufman, American playwright (This is Show Business), born in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania (d. 1961)

Elpidio Quirino

6th President of the Philippines (1949-53), born in Vigan, Ilocos Sur, Philippines

George Seldes, American investigative journalist, born in Alliance Colony, New Jersey (d. 1995)

Guo Moruo, Chinese scholar and writer, born in Leshan, Sichuan, China (d. 1978)

Cornelis Jakob van der Klauw, Dutch biologist and zoologist, born in Amsterdam (d. 1972)

Richard von Coudenhove-Kalergi, Austrian-Japanese politician, born in Tokyo, Japan (d. 1972)

Eduard Bagritsky, Russian-Soviet poet and journalist (South-West), born in Odessa, Russian Empire (d. 1934)

1895 Michael Arlen [Dikran Kouyoumdjian], British author and scriptwriter (An American Verdict), born in Ruse, Bulgaria (d. 1956)

Joan Lindsay, Australian author (Picnic at Hanging Rock), born in St Kilda East, Victoria, Australia (d. 1984)

Oswald Mosley

British politician and founder of British Union of Fascists, born in London

Choudhary Rehmat Ali, Pakistani nationalist (one of the earliest proponents of the creation of the state of Pakistan and recognized as the creator of the name “Pakistan” for a separate Muslim, homeland in South Asia and is known as the founder of the Pakistan National Movement), born in Garhshankar, Punjab, British India (d. 1951)

Warren Sturgis McCulloch, American neurophysiologist and psychiatrist ("A Logical Calculus of the Ideas Immanent in Nervous Activity" with Walter Pitts), born in Orange, New Jersey (d. 1969)

Mary Margaret McBride, American radio personality (WOR-AM, NYC), born in Paris, Missouri (d. 1976)

Frederik van der Meer, Dutch archaeologist and art historian, born in Bolsward (d. 1994)

1904 Nnamdi Azikiwe, 1st President of Nigeria (1963-66), born in Zungeru, Northern Nigeria Protectorate (d. 1996)

Sœur Emmanuelle, Belgian-French religious sister, born in Brussels, Belgium (d. 2008)

Anton [Tom] Koolhaas, Dutch author (Gekke Witte), born in Utrecht, Netherlands (d. 1992)

Daws Butler, American animation voice (Yogi Bear, Huckleberry Hound), born in Toledo, Ohio (d. 1988)

Gene Amdahl, American computer scientist who designed the IBM mainframe, born in Flandreau, South Dakota (d. 2015)

José Saramago

Portuguese writer, novelist (Blindness, The Gospel According to Jesus Christ) and Nobel laureate, born in Azinhaga, Santarém, Portugal

Joep de Boer, Dutch naval officer and politician (CDA), born in Venlo, Netherlands (d. 2006)

Michel Jouvet, French neuroscientist and medical researcher who discovered the region of the brain that controls rapid eye movement (REM sleep), born in Lons-le-Saunier, Jura, France (d. 2017)

Renate Rubinstein, German-Dutch author and columnist (Tamar), born in Berlin (d. 1990)

Alice Adams, American sculptor, born in New York City [1]

Chinua Achebe

Nigerian poet and novelist (Things Fall Apart, Christmas in Biafra), born in Ogidi, Anambra, Nigeria

1930 Salvatore Riina, Italian mobster and chief of the Sicilian Mafia, born in Corleone, Sicily, Italy (d. 2017)

1930 Walter Cole [stage name Darcelle XV] American drag performer (Portland's Darcelle XV Showplace, aged 85 became world’s oldest drag performer), born in Portland, Oregon (d. 2023) [1]

Luciano Bottaro, Italian comic book artist, born in Rapallo, Italy (d. 2006)

Elizabeth Drew, American journalist (Politics & Money: The Road to Corruption), born in Cincinnati, Ohio

1935 France-Albert René, 2nd President of Seychelles (1977-2004), born in Victoria, Crown Colony of Seychelles (d. 2019)

1935 Magdi Yacoub, Egyptian-British pioneering heart surgeon, born in Bilbeis, Egypt

John Moore, Australian politician (Minister of Defence 1998-2001), born in Rockhampton, Queensland

Robert Nozick, American philosopher (Anarchy, State, and Utopia), born in Brooklyn, New York (d. 2002)

Ann McLaughlin Korologos, 19th United States Secretary of Labor (1987-89), born in Chatham, New Jersey

Hugo Dittberner, German writer, born in Gieboldehausen, Germany

1944 Oliver Braddick, British psychologist (research on infant visual perception)

Aline Issermann, French director (Amant Magnifiquew), born in Paris, France

1948 Bonnie Greer, American-British playwright and critic, born in Chicago, Illinois

Carl J. Meade, Major USAF and NASA astronaut (STS 38, STS 50, 64), born in Chanute Air Force Base, Illinois

Piero Falchetta, Italian archivist (Biblioteca Marciana), born in Venice, Italy

1952 Robin McKinley, American writer (The Hero and the Crown), born in Warren, Ohio

Andrea Barrett, American novelist (Servants of the Map), born in Boston, Massachusetts

1954 Dick Gross, Australian politician

Pierre Larouche, Canadian National Hockey League player

Frank Milton "Pete" Higgins II, VP (Microsoft Desktop)

Boris Krivokapić, Serbian academic

1958 Roberto Guerrero, Medelin Colombia, Indy racer (Rookie of Year 1984)

Tahir Shah, British travel writer and explorer

1966 Tricia Cast, Medford NY, actress (Amanda-Bad News Bear, Young & Restless)

Craig Arnold, American poet

Danny Wallace, British author, born in Dundee, United Kingdom

Santiago Peña, Paraguayan politician and economist (President of Paraguay 2023-), born in Asunción, Paraguay

Tony Frias, American footballer, born in Hudson, Massachusetts

Carol Huynh, 2008 Canadian Gold Medalist (48 kg. wrestling), born in Hazelton, Canada

1980 Nicole Gius, Italian alpine skier, born in Schlanders, Italy

Sanna Marin, Finnish politician, youngest-ever Prime Minister of Finland (2019-23), born in Helsinki, Finland
